      "span_text": "Kiliszek et al. noticed that some uridines involved in U-U pairs tilt towards the minor groove, breaking the palindromic symmetry in a seemingly random manner over the structure. The number of CUG repeats determines the number of available three-dimensional U-U structures and hence, in longer RNA chains, there must exist a vast repertoire of U-U pair in terms of available conformations."
